1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,611
5.

2
00:00:00,961 --> 00:00:02,451
Smile Big.

3
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:07,971
Most folks have heard at one time or another that a smile will give them a real boost.

4
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:13,250
They've been told that a smile is excellent medicine for confidence deficiency.

5
00:00:13,361 --> 00:00:20,051
But lots of people still don't really believe this because they've never tried smiling when they feel fear.

6
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:22,211
Make this little test.

7
00:00:22,401 --> 00:00:26,211
Try to feel defeated and smile big at the same time.

8
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:27,330
You can't.

9
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:29,971
A big smile gives you confidence.

10
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:35,571
A big smile beats fear, rolls away worry, defeats despondency.

11
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:40,370
And a real smile does more than cure just your ill feeling.

12
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:45,411
A real smile melts away the opposition of others, and instantly too.

13
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:51,411
Another person simply can't be angry with you if you give them a big sincere smile.

14
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:56,131
Just the other day, a little incident happened to me that illustrates this.

15
00:00:56,401 --> 00:01:00,931
I was parked at an intersection, waiting for the light to change, when bam,

16
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:07,091
the driver behind me had let his foot slip the brake and put my rear bumper to a test.

17
00:01:07,361 --> 00:01:10,531
I looked back through my mirror and saw him getting out.

18
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:17,011
I got out too, and forgetting the rule book, started preparing myself for verbal combat.

19
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:21,250
I confess I was ready verbally to bite him to pieces.

20
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:26,451
But fortunately, before I got the chance, he walked up to me, smiled,

21
00:01:26,451 --> 00:01:31,971
and said in the most earnest voice, Friend, I really didn't mean to do that.

22
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:36,691
That smile, matched with his sincere comment, melted me.

23
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:41,330
I mumbled something about, that's okay, happens all the time.

24
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:47,810
Almost in less time than it takes to wink an eye, my opposition turned into friendship.

25
00:01:48,401 --> 00:01:52,611
Smile big and you feel like happy days are here again.

26
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,211
But smile big.

27
00:01:54,401 --> 00:01:57,651
A half-developed smile is not fully guaranteed.

28
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,131
Smile until your teeth show.

29
00:02:00,401 --> 00:02:03,890
That large-size smile is fully guaranteed.

30
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:09,491
I've heard many times, yes, but when I fear something or when I'm angry,

31
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:11,411
I don't feel like smiling.

32
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,091
Of course you don't.

33
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,290
No one does.

34
00:02:14,401 --> 00:02:19,011
The trick is to tell yourself forcefully, I'm going to smile.

35
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,011
Then, smile.

36
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,411
Harness the power of smiling.

